ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 01. a) Morning sleeps: duration (minutes)
01. b) Afternoon sleeps: duration (minutes)
01. c) Evening sleeps: duration (minutes)
01. d) Night sleeps: duration (minutes)
"02. Over the past week, on average how many sleeps did your baby have during the day?  "
"03. Over the past week, how often on average did your  baby wake up in the night?  "
04. a) Daytime sleeps: time to settle (minutes)
04. b) Evening sleeps: time to settle (minutes)
04. c) Night sleeps: time to settle (minutes)
"05. a) Over the past week, on average how much time during the day (5am to 6pm) did your baby cry?   (minutes) "
"05. b) Over the past week, on average how much time during the evening (6pm to 10pm) did your baby cry?   (minutes)  "
"05. c) Over the past week, on average how much time during the night (10pm to 5am) did your baby cry?  "
"06. Over the past week, how content was your baby during the day?  "
Notes: 1 = Never content by him/herself; 5 = Always content by him/herself; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 07. Over the past week how much were you bothered   by the need of your baby to have your attention during   the day?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. a) How long it took you to get your baby settled for daytime sleeps?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. b) How long it took you to get your baby settled for   the first sleep at night?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. c) How long it took you to get your baby resettled  during the night?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. d) The amount your baby slept during the day?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. e) The amount your baby slept during the night?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. f) The amount your baby cried during the daytime?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. g) The amount your baby cried during the evening?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 08. h) The amount your baby cried during the night?
Notes: 1 = Did not bother me at all; 5 = Bothered me greatly; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 09. Over the past week how did your baby wake up   after a daytime sleep?
Notes: 1 = Always woke with crying and needing comforting; 5 = Always content for a while after waking; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 10. a) How confident are you in your ability to calm and   settle your baby if he/she is unsettled?
Notes: 1 = Not at all confident; 5 = Very confident; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 10. b) How confident are you in the ability of your partner to calm and settle your baby if he/she is   unsettled?
Notes: 1 = Not at all confident; 5 = Very confident; -9 = Missing value

ElementDescription: 11. a) He/she was hungry
11. b) He/she was in pain
11. c) He/she needed changing
11. d) He/she was tired
11. e) I could not be sure what was causing it
11. f) He/she is just that sort of baby
11. g) It felt like I was doing something wrong
11. h) It felt like my baby was trying to make things   difficult for me
11. i) Other
11. Describe other
12. Any other comments regarding the sleep and settling of your baby?
SleepSettle - Total Bother score
SleepSettle - Total Confidence score
SleepSettle - Total Confidence Partner score
SleepSettle - Total Bother cutoff
SleepSettle - Total Confidence cutoff
SleepSettle - Total Confidence Partner cutoff
